. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;What creatures would dwell in such a forest&quot; she wondered. She found it hard to imagine that any harm could come from woods as magnificent as these....but yet she felt uneasy. Unlike the Misty Thicket that surrounded Rivervale, this forest had eyes and ears. Still, it was far more safe than the Dark Woods on the other side of the town, for in Kithicor the undead slept during the day, and the sunlight never seemed to shine and very difficult for a little hobbit to find her way by nightfall. <br>
Melluny continued down the path. The music got louder and the forest seemed to be getting brighter. She took a few more paces and stopped, wide-eyed and breathless. It was nothing less than she had imagined, and the legends she had heard did no justice to its magnificence. There in front of her stood Felwithe, and outside it two High Elf paladins wearing fine elven plate guarded the gates. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Hail, young one. What is your name, and what brings a halfling such as yourself to Faydwer?&quot; said one of the guards. &quot;I am Melluny, a young cleric of Bristlebane. I left Rivervale to see new lands, we young hobbits are quite curious and adventurous. I do not care to live safely within the thicket forever, and I have ever so often dreamt about Elves and so wished to see them with my own eyes.&quot; she replied with a smile. The two guards chuckled. &quot;Very well young hobbit, our city has plenty of inns, we hope you shall find them most accomidating. I am Guard Highmoon, and this is Guard Crystalwind. If you need assistance while outside of the city walls we will gladly aide you.&quot; Melluny curtsied and thanked them, then continued inside the city.  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/jscherrer/aiene.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
&quot;I feel your chill as I inhale the urge to kill all my emotions...&quot;<br>
<br>
