<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=335326" target="top">magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aiene01>aiene01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 163<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/4/03 6:47:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Adventures~</span><hr size=1> Felwithe, the City of the High Elves. No tale she had ever heard had accuratly described this place. It was far too magnificent, far too magical for any words to capture. The stone walls were covered in leaves and vines, and the water was crystal clear. The halls were marble with gold trim.<br>
Thuthud... thuthud... thuthud. An elf on a brilliant white steed rode past her and down the hall. Melluny followed after him, but his horse was far too fast for her to keep up with. She stopped to catch her breath. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Well hello there! You look mighty tired, as if you have been travelling. Are you by any chance the one here to deliver my note?&quot;  Melluny turned around and saw a tanned elf standing in front of her. 'Wow a wood elf!'  she thought to herself.  &quot;I am here because I am travelling yes, but to deliver a note, no.&quot; she replied. &quot;Hrm, I really need this note delivered to Kelethin, and I have too much going on here to do it myself so I asked Jacub to send someone, but no one has showed up.&quot; he sighed. &quot;Oh to Kelethin you say? I will deliver it to Kelethin, I would ever so much love to see it.&quot;  &quot;Most excellent!&quot;  the elf clapped in delight, &quot;Take this note to Jacub in the Bard's guild there, tell him Tacar sent you. I assure you, you will be properly rewarded for your time. Thank you ever so much!&quot; Melluny bowed. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Night came and Melluny had found a comfortable inn for the night. Felwithe was as beautiful as ever under the moonlight. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/jscherrer/aiene.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
&quot;I feel your chill as I inhale the urge to kill all my emotions...&quot;<br>
<br>
