&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;This is a strange forest indeed.&quot;  she thought to herself, for she had been walking twenty minutes and had not seen a creature other than bats and bees. She had always envisioned that the Faydwer forests would be filled with magical creatures, she figured that if she payed more attention, or was quieter, she would see them. She took each step carefully and silently. Wide-eyed and barely breathing she continued down the path and deeper into the forest. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Ten more minutes passed, and Melluny started feeling...odd. The sounds of elven music and chatter had stopped, and she felt as if she was being followed. Melluny spun around, scanning the trees. <br>
&quot;Who is there? Show yourself!&quot; she commanded, shaking a little bit. <br>
Silence.  <br>
She turned back around and walked a few more steps, then snuck behind a tree and out of sight. Scared to breathe, she stayed hidden for what seemed like five minutes, but in reality was only about forty five seconds. The trees swayed as a breeze blew thru the forest, and the world seemed to set a little bit. Melluny all of a sudden realised that she was quite hungry, for she had not eaten a thing for at least three hours. Off in the bushes she heard a strange twinkling. She perked up and peered around curiously. From out of a shrub near by came a faerie singing. Her voice carried thru the air strong and clear. She sang in a tongue that Melluny could not understand. Melluny sat there in awe watching as the faerie crossed the path. She was so dainty, and so magical, she was the most wonderful thing Melluny had ever seen. Her wings were pale pink and trimmed with silver, and she wore a tiny little dress made with the finest silk thread. Her voice was incredibly strong and high pitched, Melluny was mesmorized by it. Her song seemed happy, perhaps a tale of some sort, but about what Melluny could never guess. <br>
Melluny took a deep breath and quietly started down the path again, cautiously. Something wasnt quite right. She looked around and noticed that the forest had gotten darker. The trees in this part of the wood seemed to ache, as if in deep dispair. The path reached a dead end.  Melluny found herself standing in the middle of Faydark, lost and alone. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/jscherrer/aiene.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
&quot;I feel your chill as I inhale the urge to kill all my emotions...&quot;<br>
