&quot;Which way did i come from...&quot; she tried to remember, and decided to go to the right. As she walked the trees became less thick and there was a heavy fog. <br>
Snap.   Melluny spun around.<br>
&quot;Orc stomp orc kill your blood will spill!&quot;  shouted a vile creature waving its club at her. Melluny shrieked and started to run as fast as her short legs could carry her, which was surprisingly fast as halflings are nimble folk. She stopped as she heard it howl in pain and turned around. The creature was laying on the ground dead, purple blood spilling from its body, and a high elf in gold plate armor stood wiping the blood from his blade. Melluny blinked.<br>
&quot;Hail M'lady&quot; the elf said. &quot;You look like you could use some help. I have been in this area for awhile hunting wasps and I have been keeping a secret eye on you in case you needed assistance.&quot; <br>
&quot;I was right, i was being followed!&quot; she exclaimed &quot;thank you sir, i do not know what i would have done had you not killed that dispicible creature. Might I ask your name?&quot;<br>
&quot;I am Decepi, a humble paladin of Tunare&quot; he smiled.<br>
&quot;My name is Melluny, I have come from Rivervale and I am in search of Kelethin. What was that creature, and are there more around? I never imagined I would see such a filthy vile creature in woods like these.&quot;<br>
&quot;These woods are indeed beautiful, but there is a part of it that is dying, and it is no place for a young cleric such as yourself. A few years back an army of Orcs  invaded Kelethin, together the Elves defended their lands and managed to drive them to an area we now call Crushbone. The trees around Crushbone are in pain, the orcs are not good to their lands. They have riots and fires, and they are cruel to any living animal. Horrible vile creatures they are. Bred purely to destroy, and there is much to destroy in Faydark.&quot; he said with a look of disgust. Melluny looked around. <br>
&quot;I stumbled into an area that seemed to ache at the end of a path. Was  I anywhere near Crushbone?&quot; <br>
&quot;Yes M'lady, had you taken a few more steps and I would have stopped you.&quot; Decepi replied.<br>
&quot;Oh...&quot; <br>
&quot;Come now M'lady, I will escort you safely to Kelethin.&quot;  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/jscherrer/aiene.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
